<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="164" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-07-18"><hi rend="italic">July 18,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Conger reports that greatly modified conditions for the restoration
                            of Tientsin have been accepted by the Chinese Government, and that the
                            transfer will take place in a month.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>